description:
Prevent Flash of Unstyled Content (wrong theme flash) on page load:

Add inline script to _document.tsx that runs before React hydrates:

```tsx
<Head>
  <script dangerouslySetInnerHTML={{
    __html: `
      (function() {
        const theme = localStorage.getItem('theme');
        const systemDark = window.matchMedia('(prefers-color-scheme: dark)').matches;

        if (theme === 'dark' || (theme === 'system' && systemDark) || (!theme && systemDark)) {
          document.documentElement.classList.add('dark');
        }
      })();
    `
  }} />
</Head>
```

This must be:
- Inline (not external file)
- In <head> (runs before body renders)
- Synchronous (no async/defer)

The script applies dark class immediately based on:
1. Explicit user preference in localStorage
2. System preference if 'system' selected or no preference saved

Enable dark mode in Tailwind configuration:

Changes to tailwind.config.ts:
```typescript
export default {
  darkMode: 'class',  // Add this line
  content: [...],
  theme: {
    extend: {
      // Add dark mode typography variants
      typography: (theme) => ({
        DEFAULT: { ... },
        dark: {
          css: {
            color: theme('colors.gray.300'),
            a: { color: theme('colors.blue.400') },
            h1: { color: theme('colors.gray.100') },
            h2: { color: theme('colors.gray.100') },
            h3: { color: theme('colors.gray.100') },
            code: {
              color: theme('colors.red.400'),
              backgroundColor: theme('colors.gray.800'),
            },
            pre: {
              backgroundColor: theme('colors.gray.800'),
            },
          },
        },
      }),
    },
  },
}
```

This enables the `dark:` prefix for all utilities.
